    <section class="gradient_background">
    <div class="mealscontain">
        <h2 class="py-5 fw-bold">Your Nutrition Plan</h2>
        <div class="row featurette">
            <div class="col-md-7">
    
        <div class="meal-card p-5">
        <% if (bmi < 18.5) { %>
            <h2 class="pt-2 pb-5 fw-bold">Underweight (BMI < 18.5): Nutrient-dense meal options to promote healthy weight gain.</h2>
            <ul style="text-align: left;">
                <li>Include a source of lean protein (chicken, fish, tofu, lentils) in each meal.</li>
                <li>Incorporate plenty of fruits and vegetables for fiber, vitamins, and minerals.</li>
                <li>Choose whole grains (quinoa, brown rice, whole grain bread) over refined grains.</li>
                <li>Include healthy fats from sources like avocado, nuts, seeds, and olive oil.</li>
                <li>Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water throughout the day.</li>
            </ul>
        <% } else if (bmi >= 18.5 && bmi <= 24.9) { %>
            <h2 class="pt-2 pb-5 fw-bold">Normal Weight (BMI 18.5 - 24.9): Balanced diet plans to maintain optimal health and well-being.</h2>
            <ul style="text-align: left;">
                <li>Aim for a colorful plate by incorporating a variety of fruits and vegetables.</li>
                <li>Choose whole grains over refined grains for added fiber and nutrients.</li>
                <li>Include a source of lean protein (such as poultry, fish, tofu, or legumes) with each meal.</li>
                <li>Incorporate healthy fats from sources like nuts, seeds, avocado, and olive oil.</li>
                <li>Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water throughout the day.</li>
            </ul>
        <% } else if (bmi >= 25 && bmi <= 29.9) { %>
            <h2 class="pt-2 pb-5 fw-bold">Overweight (BMI 25 - 29.9): Strategies to support weight loss and improve metabolic health.</h2>
            <ul style="text-align: left;">
                <li>Choose lean protein sources such as chicken, turkey, fish, tofu, and legumes.</li>
                <li>Incorporate plenty of non-starchy vegetables to add volume and fiber to your meals.</li>
                <li>Opt for whole grains like quinoa, brown rice, and whole wheat bread over refined grains.</li>
                <li>Limit added sugars, processed foods, and high-calorie snacks.</li>
                <li>Practice portion control and mindful eating to avoid overeating.</li>
            </ul>
        <% } else { %>
            <h2 class="pt-2 pb-5 fw-bold">Obese (BMI â‰¥ 30): Tailored meal plans to manage weight effectively and reduce the risk of obesity-related complications.</h2>
        <ul style="text-align: left;">
            <li>Drink plenty of water throughout the day to stay hydrated and support digestion</li>
            <li>Practice portion control by using smaller plates and bowls to avoid overeating.</li>
            <li>Include a variety of colorful fruits and vegetables to ensure a range of nutrients.</li>
            <li>Limit processed foods, sugary snacks, and high-calorie beverages like soda and juice.</li>
            <li>Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise most days of the week, as approved by your healthcare provider.</li>
        </ul>
        <% } %>
        </div>
    </div>
    </div>
    </div>
